[[File:Digital_nomad.jpg|thumb]]'''数字游民'''（{{lang-en|Digital Nomads}}）这个词首次由前日立公司的CEO牧本次雄在其1997年出版的同名著作中提出<ref>T. Makimoto, D. Manners (1997), Digital Nomad (New York: John Wiley & Sons).</ref>。它是指通过[[电信|电信]]技术(尤其是[[互联网|互联网]]）来移动办公，以支持生活和旅行的一种生活方式。<ref>{{cite web |last1= Mohn |first1= Tanya |title= How To Succeed At Becoming A Digital Nomad |url= https://www.forbes.com/sites/tanyamohn/2014/03/19/tips-for-becoming-a-successful-digital-nomad/#70f7bd682744 |access-date= 2021-02-01 |archive-date= 2021-03-08 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210308015924/https://www.forbes.com/sites/tanyamohn/2014/03/19/tips-for-becoming-a-successful-digital-nomad/#70f7bd682744 |dead-url= no }}</ref>中文数字游民生活方式主题博客[https://jarodise.com/ 数字游民部落] {{Wayback|url=https://jarodise.com/ |date=20210128052648 }}给这种生活方式下了一个更为具体的定义: 数字游民是一种被数字信息技术赋能的全新生活方式，它的受众特指那些完全依靠互联网创造收入，并借此打破工作与工作地点间的强关系，达成地理位置自由和时间自由，并尽享地理套利红利，全球移动生活的人群。<ref>{{cite web |title= 什么是数字游民生活方式？(后疫情时代升级版扫盲贴) |url= https://jarodise.com/the-ultimate-guide-to-digital-nomad-lifestyle-2022-post-pandemic-version}}</ref>数字游民们通常在不同的城市，甚至在不同的国家进行远程工作。他们可能在咖啡店、[[公共图书馆|公共图书馆]]、公用办公空间甚至[[露营车|露营车]]工作。<ref>{{cite web |title= Digital Nomad Definition |url= http://sassyzengirl.com/digital-nomad-definition/ |access-date= 24 August 2016 |archive-date= 2021-02-24 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20210224074031/https://sassyzengirl.com/digital-nomad-definition/ |dead-url= no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= https://diydifm.com/blog/how-to-become-a-digital-nomad |title= How to become a digital nomad |work= DIY DIFM |access-date= November 19, 2017 |archive-date= 2018-08-01 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180801220901/https://diydifm.com/blog/how-to-become-a-digital-nomad |dead-url= no }}</ref>他们通过使用连接互联网的[[计算机|计算机]]、[[智能手机|智能手机]]进行工作。成功的数字游民一般具有对应各种紧急状态的财务缓冲能力，同时也具有较好的自力更生和自律能力。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cook |first1=Dave |title=The freedom trap: digital nomads and the use of disciplining practices to manage work/leisure boundaries |journal=Information Technology & Tourism |date=12 March 2020}}</ref>人们因为多种不同的原因成为数字游民，常见的原因包括[[财务自由|财务自由]]和一个允许长期远程工作的职业类型。虽然数字游民因时间、地点的灵活性享有更低的生活成本、更多样的生活乐趣，他们有时也受到孤独等心理问题的困扰。<ref>{{Cite news|last=Moss|first=Jennifer|date=2018-11-30|title=Helping Remote Workers Avoid Loneliness and Burnout|work=Harvard Business Review|url=https://hbr.org/2018/11/helping-remote-workers-avoid-loneliness-and-burnout|access-date=2020-06-12|issn=0017-8012|archive-date=2021-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308184726/https://hbr.org/2018/11/helping-remote-workers-avoid-loneliness-and-burnout|dead-url=no}}</ref>这种工作生活方式也面临一些其他挑战，例如在外国保持国际健康保险，熟悉和遵守当地法律，以及保持合法工作的签证身份等。

由于[[2019冠状病毒病疫情|COVID-19疫情]]，不少国家大城市的居民开始考虑在其他地方开始工作。一些旅游胜地也开始聚焦于数字游民市场，以弥补疫情造成的游客缺失。<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/travel-leisure/article/3109717/digital-nomads-find-opportunities-during-coronavirus | title = Digital nomads find opportunities during the coronavirus pandemic, and adjust to living in one place rather than travelling | work = SCMP | date = 2020-11-15 | accessdate = 2021-01-31 | archive-date = 2021-02-02 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210202041035/https://www.scmp.com/lifestyle/travel-leisure/article/3109717/digital-nomads-find-opportunities-during-coronavirus | dead-url = no }}</ref>包括[[百慕大|百慕大]]、[[安提瓜和巴布达|安提瓜和巴布达]]、[[巴巴多斯|巴巴多斯]]、[[爱沙尼亚|爱沙尼亚]]（参见{{Link-en|爱沙尼亚e居民签证|e-Residency of Estonia|}}）、[[泰国|泰国]]、[[格鲁吉亚|格鲁吉亚]]在内的多国，都通过特殊的签证项目来欢迎高收入、高素质的数字游民前往其领土生活居住。<ref>{{Cite news | url = https://www.independent.co.uk/travel/news-and-advice/remote-working-digital-nomads-visas-coronavirus-b419696.html | title = REMOTE WORKING: BEST VISAS AROUND THE WORLD FOR ADVENTUROUS DIGITAL NOMADS | work = Independent | date = 2020-10-22 | accessdate = 2021-01-31 | archive-date = 2021-01-11 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210111133730/https://www.independent.co.uk/travel/news-and-advice/remote-working-digital-nomads-visas-coronavirus-b419696.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

